Time Spent / Time at Risk

Library for algorithms to generate time spent / time at risk models.

  • Ambient population constrained models.

Kernels

K_exp = function(d, par){with(par,{
  exp(-r*(d/scl)^pwr) 
})}
pars = list(r=.1, scl=50, pwr=2)
xx = seq(0, 500, length.out = 100)
plot(xx, K_exp(xx,pars), type = "l")

Algorithms

Ambient Gravity

makeTaR_amb = function(P, v, stay, XY, par){with(par,{
  nP= length(P)
  dst = as.matrix(dist(XY, diag=TRUE, upper=TRUE))
  Psi = par$kernel(dst,pars)*P^2 
  diag(Psi)<-0 
  A = Psi %*% P 
  Psi1 = diag(v*P/as.vector(A)) %*% Psi 
  diag(Psi1) = stay
  Psi2 = diag(1-stay) %*% diag(1/rowSums(Psi)) %*% Psi
  diag(Psi2) <- stay 
  pmin(Psi1,Psi2)
})}
ambientReport = function(P, v, Psi){
  A = Psi %*% P  
  diag(Psi) -> stay  
  diag(Psi) <- 0  
  An = Psi %*% P  
  Ar = A - An
  tour = An/A 
  plot(v, tour)
  segments(0,0,1,1)
  data.frame(ix = round(1000*tour)/10, v=round(1000*v)/10, A, P, Ar, An, stay) 
}
set.seed(43)
N = 30
x = runif(N, -100, 100)
y = runif(N, -100, 100)
xy = cbind(x,y)
dxy = as.matrix(dist(xy, diag=T, upper=T))
#Psi = exp(-.1*Dxy)
P = 5^runif(N, 1,5)
#A = Psi%*% P
v = rbeta(N, 8, 100)
v[1:5] = .2
stay = rbeta(N, 95, 5)
par = list() 
par$kernel = K_exp 
par$pars = list(r=.02, scl=20, pwr=1.5)
#PsiA = diag(v*P/as.vector(A)) %*% Psi 
makeTaR_default = function(P, XY, dXY){
  nP = length(P)
  v = rbeta(nP, 8, 100) 
  stay = rbeta(nP, 95, 5) 
  r = 1/quantile(as.vector(dXY), .1)
  scl = quantile(as.vector(dXY), .2)
  par = list() 
  par$kernel = K_exp 
  par$pars = list(r=r,scl=scl,pwr=2) 
  makeTaR_amb(P, v, stay, XY, par) 
}
TaR = makeTaR_default(P, xy, dxy) 
#ambientReport(P, v, TaR) -> report
plot(xy, cex = log10(P))
for(i in 1:N) for(j in c(1:10)[-i]) arrows(x[j],y[j],x[i],y[i], lwd=50*TaR[i,j])
